msgid "## 5 Online Service Deployment"
msgstr ""

msgid "!!! note"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"In this tutorial, we suppose you downloaded the model weight to "
"`/root/.cache/modelscope/hub/models/vllm-ascend/`. Feel free to change it to"
" your own path."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"It is recommended that the following service code be encapsulated in a .sh "
"script file and executed in Bash mode."
msgstr ""

msgid "### 5.1 Single-Node Online Deployment"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"- `--max-model-len` specifies the maximum context length - that is, the sum of input and output tokens for a single request. Adjust it according to your actual scenario.\n"
"- `--no-enable-prefix-caching` indicates that prefix caching is disabled. To enable it, remove this option.\n"
"- `--speculative-config` configures the MTP (Multi-Token Prediction) speculative decoding to accelerate inference.\n"
"- `--compilation-config '{\"cudagraph_mode\":\"FULL_DECODE_ONLY\"}'` enables full ACL graph execution in the decode phase to reduce scheduling latency.\n"
"- `--async-scheduling` enables asynchronous scheduling to overlap CPU scheduling with NPU computation.\n"
"- `VLLM_ASCEND_ENABLE_FLASHCOMM1=1` enables the FlashComm communication optimization."
msgstr ""

msgid "### 5.2 Multi-Node PD Separation Deployment"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"1. **Prefill preemption interrupts Decode**: Prefill is a compute-intensive task that processes the entire input context at once, while Decode generates tokens one by one. When a new user request arrives, its Prefill phase can preempt and interrupt ongoing Decode tasks, causing jitter and higher time-per-output-token (TPOT) latency.\n"
"2. **Inflexible resource allocation**: Prefill and Decode have fundamentally different computational characteristics — Prefill is compute-bound and memory-bandwidth-intensive, while Decode is memory-bandwidth-bound. Running them on the same hardware forces a compromise that satisfies neither optimally."
msgstr ""

msgid "#### 5.2.1 A3 Series PD Separation Deployment"
msgstr ""

msgid "1. Prepare the script `launch_online_dp.py` on each node."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"|Parameter|Type|Required|Default|Description|\n"
"    |---------|----|--------|-------|-----------|\n"
"    |`--dp-size`|int|Yes|-|Data parallel size (total number of DP ranks across all nodes).|\n"
"    |`--tp-size`|int|No|1|Tensor parallel size within each DP rank.|\n"
"    |`--dp-size-local`|int|No|(same as `--dp-size`)|Number of DP ranks on the current node. If not set, defaults to `--dp-size`.|\n"
"    |`--dp-rank-start`|int|No|0|Starting rank offset for data parallel ranks on this node.|\n"
"    |`--dp-address`|str|Yes|-|IP address of the data parallel master node.|\n"
"    |`--dp-rpc-port`|str|No|12345|RPC port for data parallel master communication.|\n"
"    |`--vllm-start-port`|int|No|9000|Starting port for each vLLM engine instance on this node.|"
msgstr ""

msgid "2. Prepare the script `run_dp_template.sh` on each node."
msgstr ""

msgid "1. Prefill node"
